@glowsigma95 I don't think those elves actually meant that when they said they wanted a 'kindhearted' man to mate with. What they really meant is they wanted someone they know for sure is timid, and won't abuse them/have any other malicious intent. Hence they chose the other, smaller guy instead of the bigger one; he was too threatening for them. It has nothing to do with something as complex as 'kindheartedness', people just use it as one-way thing: "that person will be nice to ME". They never even cared how you usually act to others or even what your other circumstances are in the first place. This especially holds true when you are trying to estimate people by their appearences only. But in all honesty, this is nothing more than a defense mechanism, it usually lacks any real meaning so you shouldn't get worked up about it.
